channel.description:
Alright well my dad wants a new computer that is just basic. So i am going to give him my old tower. Then in exchange he is going to get me a external hard drive. I dont really know prices so i am going to ask how much my computer is worth.
its a compaq Intel Celeron 2.8ghz processor the worst video card possible 1gb of ram Windows XP operationg system 32bit
not sure what else you need to know =\

item.title: How much is my computer worth?
item.dc:creator: @xxlegitxx xxlegitxx
item.description:
@xxlegitxx wrote:

ThAt0n36Uy:

I use a 2.2 Ghz, with 640 mb of ram on this PC. I am able to run CS3 Extended, Play WoW, and then a couple rounds of CS:Source. Before I need to reboot. Otherwise, if I’m just Chatting and working on photoshop, I can leave my PC running for 3 or 4 days. I run FireFox too, which drains it. My computer now is worth $230.00 Including a RADEON 9250. and a 27 Gb hard drive.

What is “a 2.2 GHz”? If you know anything about computers, you will realize that clock speed is one of many components that matter. Is it Intel or AMD? What is the L2 cache size? Is it dual core? Is it 64-bit?

AMD Athlon X2 64 5600+ means much more than “a 2.2 GHz.” Your RAM also blows the cock.

Let me tally up your computer for you.

2.2 GHz processor. I’ll assume it’s single core, given the rest of your computer. $40
512 MB + 128 MB RAM. $10 + $10
27 GB HDD. $20
Radeon 9250. $30

I’d say <$100 as well for your computer used.

item.dc:creator: @xxlegitxx xxlegitxx
item.description:
@xxlegitxx wrote:

[quote=“ThAt0n36Uy, post:6, topic:186001”]I don’t see how a 2.8 ghz processor sucks.

EDIT: Whats the screen size? And what version of Windows Xp, professional?[/quote]

He said a tower, not a tower + monitor.

A 2.8 GHz processor blows.

newegg.com

Intel Celeron D 336 Prescott Single-Core 2.8 GHz LGA 775 84W BX80547RE2800CN...

Buy Intel Celeron D 336 Prescott Single-Core 2.8 GHz LGA 775 84W BX80547RE2800CN Processor with fast shipping and top-rated customer service.Once you know, you Newegg!

And I’m sure it’s worth much less than $42 as stated, considering it’s been used.

1 GB RAM is probably DDR2 667, so I’d value it at $10 - $20.

Mobo I’m guessing is microatx, so I’d say $20 - $30 for that.

So a generous estimate would be $100 for the computer.
